def: One who favors protection. See Protection, 4.
A small opening; esp., one of the apertures, closed bymembranes, between the tympanum and internal ear.
Having (such) a tone; -- chiefly used in composition; as, high-toned; sweet-toned. Toned paper, paper having a slight tint, indistinction from paper which is quite white.
Falling copiously or in streams, as from a sluice.And oft whole sheets descend of sluicy rain. Dryden.
Defenseless. [Obs.]The sword awes the indefensive villager. Sir T. Herbert.
The act of excarnificating or of depriving of flesh;excarnation. Johnson.
Not to provide; to fail to provide. [Obs.] Boyle.
